\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b 15-17}).{\b  P. atrata} group. Perennials with several or many rosettes. Leaves in a basal rosette, linear-lanceolate, entire, slightly contracted at the base. Scapes terete. Bracts orbicular to suborbicular, with prominent keel and wide, membranous margin, with long hairs at apex. Sepals equal, free, almost entirely membranous, keeled to halfway or less. Corolla-tube glabrous; lobes at least 2 mm. Capsule 2-locular; seeds (1-)2-4, rugose, canaliculate on inner face.
