\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. P. atrata} Hoppe,{\i  Bot. Taschenb.}{\b  1799}: 85 (1799) ({\i P. montana }sensu Lam., non Hudson,{\i  P. fuscescens} Jordan). Leaves 5-20 × 0·5-1·5 cm, flat or slightly canaliculate, long-acuminate, green, glabrous or sparsely pubescent. Scapes as long as or longer than leaves, erect or ascending, sparsely hairy. Spike 1·5-3 cm, oblong-ovoid. Bracts entire, long-ciliate, with glabrous or sparsely pubescent keel and brown or colourless margins. Sepals long-ciliate, with brownish margin. Anthers yellowish or violet. Capsule conical; seeds 3-5 mm. 2n = 12, 24 + 0-2B, 36. {\i Mountains of C. & S. Europe.} Al Au Bu Cz Ga Ge Gr He Hs It Ju Po Rm Rs (W).
